    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-04T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="1351"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.116/361</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-04T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1915, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received September 6, 8.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1008. American schools and colleges are opening under following conditions:
                    Government demands religious exercises and instruction shall be optional for
                    non-Christians but may be obligatory for Christians. Turkish must be taught to
                    Ottomans but in lowest class only. Heavy taxes are demanded on school buildings,
                    hospitals, and lands, abrogating previous agreements and firmans. Embassy is
                    protesting. Owing to general deportation of Armenians in Asia Minor, accompanied
                    by massacres, atrocities, and starvation, schools in those provinces may not
                    open, or will open under greatest difficulties. Inform <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRJL1">Barton</persName>, Boston; <persName>Dodge,
                        Crane</persName>, <persName>Brown</persName>, New York.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgenthau</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
